page.title: 15More about wildlife.
page.content: We have deer in our block too.These deer are always seen in small groups. Most of the deer are roe deer,but there are muntjac as well.Two of our group thought they'd seen a third rare type of deer, but it was a rare breed of sheep,called a Soay sheep. These wild flowers were all fairly common in the fields and roadsides: stinging nettle,cow parsley,ox-eye daisy,plantain,yarrow,daisy,poppy,red campion,herb robert,knotgrass,bugloss, dandelion,groundsel,lesser bindweed,red deadnettle,woody nightshade,lesser celandine,common mallow,field scabious, buttercup,rosebay willowherb,red clover vetch,stitchwort,meadowsweet,ground ivy germander speedwell,wood anemone and bladder campion.
